==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saponaceous
<hw>Sap`o*na"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sapo</ets>, <ets>-onis</ets>, soap, of Teutonic origin, and akin to
E. <ets>soap</ets>. See <er>Soap</er>.]</ety> <def>Resembling soap;
having the qualities of soap; soapy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Saponaceous</xex> bodies are compounds of an acid
and a base, and are in reality a kind of salt.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1276 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><ent>Saponacity</ent>⟦br⟧
